1) write model1.mtrol, model2.mtrol, model3.mtrol, guess.mtrol 
2) run   echo [model1].mtrol | [path]/modelador3.x 
3) cp guess.mod guess1.mod & cp guess.mod guess2.mod
4) run   echo [sir1].trol | [path]/sir.x 

You can check the results using IDL graphics2.pro

___________________________________________________________________________________________________

Alternatively, you can modify the models using IDL procedures 
read_model & write_model

for instance
IDL>   
  read_model,'hsra11.mod',logtau,t,p,vmic,b,v,g,f,z,pg,ro,vmac,fill,stray
  write_model,'model1b.mod',logtau,t,p,vmic,b*0+1000,v*0.+2.e5,g*0+60.,f,z,pg,ro,vmac,fill,stray
  write_model,'model2b.mod',logtau,t,p,vmic,b*0+2000+400.*logtau,v*0.+2.e5,g*0+30.-15*logtau,f,z,pg,ro,vmac,fill,stray
  write_model,'model3b.mod',logtau,t,p,vmic,b*0+1000-400.*logtau,v*0.+2.e5+0.5e5*logtau,g*0+60+15*logtau,f,z,pg,ro,vmac,fill,stray
  write_model,'gues1b.mod',logtau,t,p,vmic,b*0+500,v*0.+1.e5,g*0+15,f,z,pg,ro,vmac,fill,stray
  write_model,'gues2b.mod',logtau,t,p,vmic,b*0+500,v*0.+1.e5,g*0+15,f,z,pg,ro,vmac,fill,stray
